FBIS3-7415 "dreas059_d_94002" FBIS-EAS-94-059 Document Type:Daily Report 26 Mar 1994 South Korea DPRK `Moving' Nuclear Facilities Around Capital SK2603005794 Seoul CHOSON ILBO in Korean 26 Mar 94 p 2 SK2603005794 Seoul CHOSON ILBO Language: Korean Article Type:BFN [AFP/YONHAP from Beijing] [Text] On 25 March, one day before President Kim Yong-sam's China visit to seek China's active role in resolving the North Korean nuclear issue, nuclear experts in Beijing said North Korea is moving its nuclear facilities under suspicion through connecting underground passages to other places in Pyongyang. Meanwhile, Beijing sources anticipate that, although President Kim will try to induce China to play an active role in resolving the North Korean nuclear issue during his five-day visit to China by using the ROK's economic strength, China will not immediately change its position on the issue.
